OL,3,C'Incredibly tense': Liz Kendall's
OL,4,Cefforts to win over Labour MPs on
OL,5,Cbenefits
OL,7,F"They don't want to engage with our
OL,8,Fconcerns, they're fixated on telling
OL,9,Fus the system is immoral," one usually
OL,10,Fsupportive MP told me. While another
OL,11,Fsaid the government were just "not in
OL,12,Flistening mode".
OL,14,FI'm told Kendall is expected to keep
OL,15,Fengaging in outreach efforts with
OL,16,FLabour MPs in the coming weeks in an
OL,17,Fattempt to ease growing discontent
OL,18,Fover the reforms.
